item.title: CVE-2018-10922|2024-08-05T07:54:35.779Z -- %5Bunknown%5D -- ttembed
item.description: An input validation flaw exists in ttembed. With a crafted input file, an attacker may be able to trigger a denial of service condition due to ttembed trusting attacker controlled values.

item.title: CVE-2018-10921|2024-08-05T07:54:36.317Z -- %5Bunknown%5D -- ttembed
item.description: Certain input files may trigger an integer overflow in ttembed input file processing. This overflow could potentially lead to corruption of the input file due to a lack of checking return codes of fgetc/fputc function calls.
